      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear that, but it feels like the \"long-term benefits\" are always being used to justify huge upfront hits that some small shops just can't survive. is there any real evidence that these regs actually provide a net positive for the environment, or is it mostly just a way to push new tech on anyone who can afford it?",
